# Axiom Gemini Guidelines

This project follows Axiom conventions.

## App Actions

- Prefer reusable Action classes in `app/Actions` for business logic.
- Name actions by what they do and keep one focused public `handle()` method.
- Inject dependencies via constructor promoted properties.
- Generate actions with `php artisan make:action "{name}" --no-interaction`.
- Use `DB::transaction()` for multi-model write flows when needed.

## Architecture

- Prefer DTOs over associative arrays at application boundaries.
- Keep controllers thin and move business logic into actions.
- Follow existing project structure and naming conventions.

## PHP And Quality

- Use `declare(strict_types=1);`.
- Prefer `final` classes and explicit typing.
- Prefer `readonly` objects when mutation is not required.
- Avoid `dd`, `dump`, or `ray` in committed code.
- Keep static analysis and formatting tools strict.

## Testing

- Add or update tests whenever behavior changes.

## Skills

- Use `.ai/skills/actions.md`, `.ai/skills/dto.md`, `.ai/skills/enum.md`, `.ai/skills/crud.md`, and `.ai/skills/quality.md`.
